    "long_instructions": "## What is an LLM?\r\n\r\n#### A large language model, or LLM, is a type of artificial intelligence system designed to understand, generate, and work with human language at a vast scale. You may be familiar with models such as ChatGPT, Gemini, or various customer support bots on websites.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### LLMs are trained on a wide array of text data and learning patterns from an extensive database. This training enables it to perform tasks like answering questions, writing text, and translating languages, based on the context and information it has learned.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Watch this video clip to hear Mira Murati, formerly of Open AI, and Cristobal Valenzuela from Runway explain how large language models work.\r\n\r\n"
  },
